
HTTP & HTTPS
🎯 Objective

Learn what HTTP and HTTPS are, how they work, their differences, common HTTP methods, status codes, SSL/TLS encryption, and how to test websites using Linux commands.

📖 What is HTTP?

HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol) is an application-layer protocol used for communication between a web browser (client) and a web server.

Whenever you open a website, your browser sends an HTTP request, and the server returns an HTTP response.

Example:

Browser  ------------HTTP Request------------>  Web Server

Browser  <-----------HTTP Response------------ Web Server
Features of HTTP
Stateless protocol
Client-server architecture
Human-readable messages
Uses TCP
Default Port: 80
What is HTTPS?

HTTPS (HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure) is the secure version of HTTP.

It encrypts communication using SSL/TLS, ensuring that data exchanged between the client and server cannot be easily intercepted or modified.

Default Port: 443



HTTP vs HTTPS

| Feature         | HTTP                        | HTTPS                              |
| --------------- | --------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Full Form       | HyperText Transfer Protocol | HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure |
| Port            | 80                          | 443                                |
| Encryption      | ❌ No                        | ✅ Yes (SSL/TLS)                    |
| Security        | Low                         | High                               |
| Data Privacy    | Not protected               | Encrypted                          |
| Authentication  | No                          | Uses digital certificates          |
| SEO             | Less preferred              | Preferred by search engines        |
| Browser Warning | May show "Not Secure"       | Shows secure connection            |


How HTTP Works
+-----------+                     +--------------+
| Browser   |                     | Web Server   |
+-----------+                     +--------------+
      |                                  |
      |------ HTTP Request ------------->|
      |                                  |
      |<----- HTTP Response -------------|
      |                                  |

How HTTPS Works
+-----------+                     +--------------+
| Browser   |                     | Web Server   |
+-----------+                     +--------------+
      |                                  |
      |------ TLS Handshake ------------>|
      |<----- Certificate ---------------|
      |------ Encrypted Request -------->|
      |<----- Encrypted Response --------|
      |                                  |


